CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper May 21, 1960, pg. 20, reads: "Free Tickets - These lucky youngsters got free tickets to the boxing matches held at the Centre Avenue YMCA. Handing out the ducats are popular Fifth Ward Constable Tommy Smith, O. T. Whiting, newly elected First District committeeman, and Robert L. Edwards Jr., YMCA physical education director. Constable Smith sponsored the show. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Thomas J. "Tommy" Smith, O. T. Whiting, and Robert L. Edwards Jr. handing out tickets for boxing match to small crowd of boys, in Centre Avenue YMCA
